    question: "How long does post-renovation cleaning take?",
    answer: "Post-renovation projects often leave behind layers of fine dust that continue to settle even after the initial cleaning. For smaller projects, one detailed cleaning is usually enough. However, for larger remodels or new builds, we may recommend a two-phase approach:\n\n• Initial Cleaning: Removes heavy dust, debris, and surface dirt.\n• Final Polish: A follow-up visit to ensure all fine dust is eliminated and surfaces are spotless before move-in.\n\nThis ensures your space looks and feels truly brand new, without lingering dust or construction residue."
  },
  {
    question: "When should I schedule this service?",
    answer: "We recommend scheduling your post-renovation cleaning after all major construction work is complete and contractors have removed large debris. This ensures we can focus on the detailed cleaning that makes your space move-in ready.\n\nFor the best results:\n• Wait for finishes to cure: Allow paint, grout, and sealants to fully dry before cleaning.\n• Confirm contractor completion: Make sure no additional work or sanding is planned, as this can create new dust.\n• Plan ahead: Book your cleaning a few days before moving furniture or unpacking, so your new space is spotless and ready to enjoy."
